    <section class="container">
        <div class="font-size-1-5em">
            <h1>About JMTS</h1>

            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>
                The <strong>Job Management &amp; Tracking System (JMTS)</strong> is 
                a Java/Jakarta EE web application designed to manage and track 
                job activities efficiently. It allows users to create, update, 
                and monitor job progress while integrating with various business modules.
            </p>

            <h2>Features</h2>
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; Job creation, assignment, and tracking
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; User role management (Admin, Manager, Employee)
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; Real-time job status updates
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; Reports and analytics
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; Secure authentication and authorization
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; <strong>Java EE (Jakarta EE)</strong> – Backend development
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; <strong>JSF (JavaServer Faces)</strong> – User interface
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; <strong>MySQL</strong> – Database management
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; <strong>Maven</strong> – Dependency and build management
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    &bullet; <strong>JPA (Eclipse)</strong> – ORM for database interaction
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Support JMTS</h2>
            <p>
                JMTS is free and open-source software dedicated to helping teams 
                manage and track jobs efficiently.
            </p>

            <p>
                If you find JMTS useful, please consider sponsoring us on 
                <a href="https://github.com/sponsors/DPBandA">GitHub</a> or supporting us 
                via <a href="https://opencollective.com/jmts">Open Collective</a> or 
                <a href="https://liberapay.com/jmts">Liberapay</a>.
            </p>

            Your contributions help us:
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item">Improve features and usability
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    Provide documentation and support
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    Maintain security and performance
                </li>
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    Sustain long-term development
                </li>
            </ul>

            Every bit of support helps keep JMTS thriving. Thank you!
